# Line-ending policy for the repo (kills the Windows "LF will be replaced by CRLF" warnings).
#
# Git for Windows sets core.autocrlf=true at the system level, which does an LF<->CRLF round-trip on
# every checkout/add and warns about it. This file overrides that PER-REPO: all text files are stored
# AND checked out as LF, so git never converts and never warns — independent of each machine's config.
# LF is also what the Linux CI (GitHub Actions / Pages build) and the deployed site expect.
* text=auto eol=lf

# Binary files: never apply text/eol conversion. The parquet lake especially must stay byte-exact.
*.parquet binary
*.png  binary
*.jpg  binary
*.jpeg binary
*.gif  binary
*.ico  binary
*.webp binary
*.pdf  binary
*.woff  binary
*.woff2 binary
